<title>GERMANY: Hesse June CPI up 0.3 pct m/m, up 1.5 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Hesse June CPI up 0.3 pct m/m, up 1.5 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>WIESBADEN, Germany 1997-06-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>The statistics office in the west German state of Hesse said on Wednesday the cost of living in June rose 0.3 percent from May for an annual rate of 1.5 percent.</p>
<p>The consumer price index for Hesse rose by 0.3 percent in May from April for an annual rate of 1.2 percent.</p>
<p>The statistics office noted in its report that food prices in June were 1.2 percent higher than in June 1996, presenting a stronger rise than had been seen in May when food prices rose 0.5 percent year on year.  </p>
<p>The statistics office gave the following breakdown of its June cost of living data :</p>
<p>    Index/component			   mth/mth   yr/yr  Index</p>
<p>    Overall price index		     +0.3	+1.5   115.5</p>
<p>    Prices exc heating oil, fuel	  +0.3	+1.5   115.6</p>
<p>    Prices exc seasonal goods	     +0.3	+1.5   115.9</p>
<p>    Rents					 +0.1	+2.3   128.4</p>
<p>    Household energy			  -0.2	+2.9   99.8</p>
<p>    Personal goods, services and other  +1.3	+1.9   125.0</p>
<p>    Transport and communications	  +0.1	+0.3   114.9</p>
<p>    Furniture and other household goods +0.0	+0.5   111.5</p>
<p>    Foodstuffs, drinks, tobacco	   +0.5	+1.5   111.2</p>
<p>    Clothing, shoes			   +0.1	+0.8   109.0</p>
<p>    Health and personal care items	+0.3	+1.6   112.5</p>
<p>    Education, entertainment, leisure   -0.1	+2.1   113.1</p>
